E! DO THE GIT BLAME ONE NEXT!! I KNOW YOU HAVE A GIT BLAME ONE!! WE ALL HAVE A GIT BLAME ONE!!\n\n*security begins approaching*\n\nNO NO NO I'M FINE, I'M FINE ΓÇö HE DESERVES A STANDING OVATION ΓÇö *standing, swaying* ΓÇö I AM standing!! SEE?! MOSTLY!!"}},"cwd":"D:\\Repositories\\max-ai-ui\\playground\\backend","taskId":"asjdlkja-1772362729187","terminalId":"12c80d64-fc1c-405e-8669-66ff0af908f6","toolResult":{"resultType":"success","textResultForLlm":"Γ£ô Task session valid ΓÇö proceeding with the heckle!\n\n---\n\n**RATING:** 8/10\n\n**REACTION:** *sloshes beer, knocks over chair standing up*\n\nOHHHHHHH SHE HASN'T REVIEWED IT YET!! ≡ƒì║ FOUR MONTHSSS!! HAHAHAHA ΓÇö\n\n*points aggressively at stage*\n\nHEY! HEY YOU! I FEEL THAT IN MY SOOOUL, MAN! MY WIFE GIVES ME THE SAME TWO LITTLE EYES AND SHE AIN'T A THERAPIST!! SHE'S JUST DISAPPOINTED!!\n\n*trips slightly on barstool*\n\nBUT LISTEN ΓÇö LISTENNN ΓÇö the \"committed branch\" bit?? COMMITTED BRANCH?? MY THERAPIST WOULD SAY THE SAME THING EXCEPT REPLACE \"BRANCH\" WITH \"TO AN INSTITUTION\"!!\n\n*wipes tear, spills more beer*\n\nYOU'RE BRILLIANT! YOU'RE A GENIUS! I HATE YOU! WHY IS THIS MY LIFE?! I HAVE FOUR OPEN PULL REQUESTS WITH MY MOTHER AND SHE HASN'T REVIEWED THOSE EITHER!!\n\n*slow clap that keeps getting faster*\n\nENCORE! ENCORE! DO THE GIT BLAME ONE NEXT!! I KNOW YOU HAVE A GIT BLAME ONE!! WE ALL HAVE A GIT BLAME ONE!!\n\n*security begins approaching*\n\nNO NO NO I'M FINE, I'M FINE ΓÇö HE DESERVES A STANDING OVATION ΓÇö *standing, swaying* ΓÇö I AM standing!! SEE?! MOSTLY!!"},"timestamp":"2026-03-01T16:36:50.1414140+05:30","sessionId":"00ab4c62-c617-4b31-b606-b061bdb13661","toolArgs":{"agent_type":"heckler","description":"Heckler rates final joke 5","mode":"sync","prompt":"You are a heckler at a comedy club. The comedian just told this CLOSING joke:\n\n\"I told my therapist I was obsessed with writing software. She said, 'Don't worry, it's just a phase.' I said, 'No no ΓÇö it's a committed branch.' She said, 'That's not what IΓÇö are you okay?' I said, 'I haven't slept in three days and I'm still getting merge conflicts with my wife.' She closed her notebook and said, 'I'm going to need you to push your feelings to a remote repository and come back in two weeks.' I opened a pull request. She hasn't reviewed it yet. It's been four months. No comments. Just two little eyes.\"\n\nThis is the FINAL joke of the night. Rate it 1-10 and give your BIGGEST heckler reaction! Format EXACTLY as:\n**RATING:** [number]/10\n**REACTION:** [heckler reaction]"}}
